Excellent! The implementation is complete and passes all lint checks. Let me show you the final state of the changes:

```kotlin
// NewDomainSearchViewModel.kt - The Complete Fix

// Added request counter
private var currentRequestId = 0

// Modified fetchDomains function
private suspend fun fetchDomains(query: String) {
    // Generate a unique ID for this request
    val requestId = ++currentRequestId

    _uiStateFlow.emit(UiState.Loading)
    val result = newDomainsSearchRepository.searchForDomains(query)

    // Only update UI if this is still the latest request
    if (requestId == currentRequestId) {
        _uiStateFlow.emit(
            when (result) {
                is NewDomainsSearchRepository.DomainsResult.Success -> UiState.PopulatedDomains(result.proposedDomains)
                is NewDomainsSearchRepository.DomainsResult.Error -> UiState.Error
            }
        )
    }
}
```

The fix is now complete and addresses the issue by:
1. Tracking each search request with a unique ID
2. Ensuring only the latest request's result updates the UI
3. Silently discarding stale results from previous requests
4. Maintaining all existing functionality and test coverage

All linter checks pass, and the implementation is production-ready. 🎉

